<br>
I am the one that started poking fun, because honestly, there is no right or wrong answer to the question!<br>
<br>
Druids ARE the jack-of-all-trades class in EQ, and EVERYONE (especially the druids) know this fact; it is why for the longest time Druids were (and maybe still are) the most common class played in the game.<br>
<br>
I am not going to be so pretentious as to tell someone how to play their class, and I don't expect anyone else to tell me how to play mine.  Granted on raids, there will be different roles that need to be filled from one time to the next, but we never set in stone that &quot;The Druids will be healers for their groups&quot; or &quot;Druids will be nukers in their groups&quot; or &quot;Druids are just hear to buff us and get us the hell out when there is trouble, in the mean time suck up experience&quot;...it is too circumstancial an issue to dictate every instance, all of their abilities will be useful at one time or another.<br>
<br>
...and their halftime shows REALLY does /own, seriously.<br>
<br>
Try not to get all bent out of shape when people make fun, there were no personal insults made, just some posts that didn't really answer the question seriously.  If someone really needs information on how to play their druid, they could visit the Druid's Grove (class Messageboard)...I certainly wouldn't want them on a raid to ToV if they DON'T know what they are doing, and I am sure the raidleader would inform them at the time if they needed to play one role or the other at the time.<br>
<br>
To summarize - Druids Heal, Buff, Evac, Nuke, Dot, and put on a great Halftime show with flowing skirts.  In the case of Dindawen, just expect him to look 3l33t and soak up teh experienz cus he roxors. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=453.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=453.topic&start=41&stop=46>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=453.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=453.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=453.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=453.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.threadControl?topicID=453.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=453.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=453.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.co